      <div xml:id="timf-infi">
        <head xml:id="timf-infi-Hd1e109">Infirmitas</head>
        <p xml:id="timf-infi-d1e111" n="a">
          <quote xml:id="timf-infi-Qd1e113">Qui ueram ostendit corporis infirmitatem, humane tractandus est; qui autem falsam
            pretendit et conuinci non potest, Deo dimittendus est.</quote>
          <ref xml:id="timf-infi-Rd1e115">Augustinus de opere monachorum.</ref>
        </p>


        <p xml:id="timf-infi-d1e118" n="b">
          <quote xml:id="timf-infi-Qd1e120">Corporis debilitas nimia eciam uires anime frangit, mentis quoque ingenium
            marcescere facit. Quicquid cum modo et temperamento fit, salutare est.</quote>
          <ref xml:id="timf-infi-Rd1e122">Ieronymus in quadam epistola.</ref>
        </p>


        <p xml:id="timf-infi-d1e125" n="c">
          <quote xml:id="timf-infi-Qd1e127">Considerata infirmitas propria, mala nobis excusat aliena.</quote>
          <ref xml:id="timf-infi-Rd1e129">Gregorius libro V. moralium.</ref>
        </p>


        <p xml:id="timf-infi-d1e132" n="d">
          <quote xml:id="timf-infi-Qd1e134">Quosdam presciens Deus multa peccare posse, flagellat eos in infirmitate corporis
            ne peccent, ut eis utilius sit frangi langoribus ad salutem, quam remanere incolumes ad
            dampnationem.</quote>
          <ref xml:id="timf-infi-Rd1e136">Hugo libro II. de anima.</ref>
        </p>


        <p xml:id="timf-infi-d1e140" n="e">
          <quote xml:id="timf-infi-Qd1e142">Quidam pro libito suo uiuunt, et semper sunt uegeti. Quidam a regulis Ypocratis non
            deuiant, et assidue sunt infirmi.</quote>
          <ref xml:id="timf-infi-Rd1e144">Petrus Rauennas in quadam epistola.</ref>
        </p>


        <p xml:id="timf-infi-d1e147" n="f">
          <quote xml:id="timf-infi-Qd1e149">In omni morbo tria grauia sunt: metus mortis, dolor corporis, intermissio
            uoluptatis.</quote>
          <ref xml:id="timf-infi-Rd1e151">Seneca LXXII. epistola.</ref>
        </p>


        <p xml:id="timf-infi-d1e154" n="g">
          <quote xml:id="timf-infi-Qd1e156">Morieris, non quia egrotas, sed quia uiuis. Cum conualueris, non mortem sed
            ualitudinem effugies.</quote>
          <ref xml:id="timf-infi-Rd1e158">Seneca ibidem.</ref>
        </p>


        <p xml:id="timf-infi-d1e161" n="h">
          <quote xml:id="timf-infi-Qd1e163">Nichil eque sanitatem impedit, sicut remediorum crebra mutatio. Non conualescit
            planta, que sepe transfertur. Nichil magis egris prodest quam ab eo curari, a quo
            uoluerit.</quote>
          <ref xml:id="timf-infi-Rd1e165">Seneca in epistola II.</ref>
        </p>


        <p xml:id="timf-infi-d1e168" n="i">
          <quote xml:id="timf-infi-Qd1e170">Bona ualitudo iocundior est eis, qui de graui morbo recreati sunt, quam qui nunquam
            egro corpore fuerunt.</quote>
          <ref xml:id="timf-infi-Rd1e172">Seneca in epistola.</ref>
        </p>


        <p xml:id="timf-infi-d1e175" n="k">
          <quote xml:id="timf-infi-Qd1e177">Bene dormit, qui non sentit, quando male dormit.</quote>
          <ref xml:id="timf-infi-Rd1e179">Seneca in prouerbiis.</ref>
        </p>

        <p xml:id="timf-infi-d1e183" n="ubi">
          <ref xml:id="timf-infi-Rd1e185">Caro ac</ref>, <ref xml:id="timf-infi-Rd1e187">ad</ref>; <ref xml:id="timf-infi-Rd1e189">Consideratio k</ref>; <ref xml:id="timf-infi-Rd1e191">Dolor d</ref>;
            <ref xml:id="timf-infi-Rd1e193">Gaudium e</ref>; <ref xml:id="timf-infi-Rd1e196">Gracia b</ref>; <ref xml:id="timf-infi-Rd1e198">Gula ai</ref>; <ref xml:id="timf-infi-Rd1e200">Medicina</ref>;
            <ref xml:id="timf-infi-Rd1e202">Sanitas</ref>; <ref xml:id="timf-infi-Rd1e204">Senectus f</ref>. </p>

